* Set magneto_s3_custom_inventory_manifest_relative_path - <prefix_we_gave_in_source_regitsration>/manifest-path

* make sure backup is completed
* after - test_delete_latest_snapshot

** Set magneto_s3_custom_inventory_manifest_relative_path - ""

column1: Nosql app certificate verification manual tests
column36:
Test app certificate updation on various nosql app builds by doing the following test steps

 
eg: if we are testing for 720 app * Disable app cert validation
 * Install an older released app (lets say 72010055)
 * Enable app cert validation
 * Run a backup
 * Upgrade the NoSQL app. ([app1011-72010057|http://artifactory.eng.cohesity.com/artifactory/cohesity-builds-imanis/INTERNAL/7.2.0/7.2/20250614-102213/apps-full/])
 * Run backup ( full and incremental, CDP), recovery (PITR and regular)

column1: MongoDB qualification execution for  GA - PITR
column36:
[https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1yHXAA4n_0ROdJCg73yfu6c4roLSb-f4So0zSPDTVgVc/edit?usp=sharing]
{code:java}
PITR -> Functionality -> Policy	t0: enable log backup; t1 : disable log backup in policy; t2: enable log backup; t3: next log backup run ; t4: data backup run; t5: log backup run validate PITR timeline from t0-t1 and t>t4
PITR -> Functionality -> Policy	PITR timeline should be hidden when policy does not contain log backup
PITR -> Negative -> OpLogDir	OpLog Slice capture stops due to no space on disk. Validate correct error message in job and op log capture resumes when space is available.
PITR -> Functionality -> OpLogDir	Validate timeline and hole when: t0: successful log backup ; t1: space full on disk ; t2: job failed ; t3: space available; t4: next successful log backup run ; t5: next incremental; Timeline should be visible t0-t1 and >t5.
PITR -> Functionality -> Node Selection	Re-sync the selected node in the between two op-log backup intervals. Next oplog backup should be verified, and perform recovery to before and after resync operation.
PITR -> Functionality -> Node Selection -> ReplicationDelay	log backup and Data backup at t0 ; log backup at t1; at t2 selected node is down and other node n2 is having sync delay of 10 minutes ; t3: next log backup occurs from n2; Validate log backup, timeline at t1, t2 and perform recovery to t2
PITR -> Functionality -> Node Selection -> ReplicationDelay	log backup and Data backup at t0 ; log backup at t1 from node having sync delay of 10 minutes ; validate timeline from t0 to t1 and recovery to t1
PITR -> Functionality -> Node Selection -> ReplicationDelay	log backup and Data backup at t0 ; log backup at t1; add replication delay of 10 minutes to node at t2 ; log backup at t3 ; validate PITR timeline from t0 - t3 and recovery to t3.
PITR -> Functionality -> Node Selection -> ReplicationDelay	add replication delay of 10 minutes to secondary ; log and Data backup at t0 ; log backup at t1; remove replication delay at t2 ; log backup at t3 ; validate PITR timeline from t0 - t3 and recovery to t3 and t2
PITR -> Sharding -> ConfigDB	For a sharded environment, add a replication delay to the the configDB member added as the preferredNode: validate log backup and check for holes {code}

column1: Periodic cleanup and trigger of IBM Baas train runs
column36:
We would like to ensure a periodic trigger of IBM Baas automation train at least once a week. Consult with the team members on which build to trigger on ibm_baas_automation channel. We don't yet want to spend any cycles on ibm2_rm. Current goal will be to trigger upgrade train - upgrading from last released build of [7.2.13 to|http://7.2.to/] latest 7.2.14 build. 

This also involves cleaning up the previous cluster, VSI rigel and VSI source instances.
